70.4	Rigoletto	Rigoletto	Rigoletto is an opera in three acts by Giuseppe Verdi. The Italian libretto was written by Francesco Maria Piave based on the play Le roi s'amuse by Victor Hugo. It was first performed at La Fenice in Venice on March 11, 1851. It is considered by many to be the first of the operatic masterpieces of Verdi's middle-to-late career.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/51/Verdi.jpg/220px-Verdi.jpg
